\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Installing in Mac OS X
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs32 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Before Installing:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf2 It is recommended that you quit applications before installing fonts. Certain applications will update their font menus automatically, but most will require a relaunch.
\fs32 \cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Using a Font Management Utility:
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf2 If you are using a a font management utility such as Suitcase or FontExplorer, follow the installation instructions provided with that software.\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs32 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Using Font Book:
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf2 Later versions of OS X include Font Book. To install fonts using Font Book, simply double-click on the font file(s) in the Finder. A Font Book preview window will open. Click the "Install Font" button.\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs32 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Direct Installation:
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf2 If you do not have Font Book or a management utility, you will need to install the font(s) directly into your system. There are various locations in which fonts can be installed, including the Library folder within your Home folder. For detailed information on the best option for you, visit Apple's website (including {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://docs.info.apple.com/article.html?artnum=106417"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 http://docs.info.apple.com/article.html?artnum=106417}}). Once you determine the best folder for your needs, copy the OpenType font file(s) into it.\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs32 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Classic Installation:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf2 To use OpenType fonts in Classic mode you will need to install the fonts in the Classic System Folder. See the instructions below for Installing in Mac OS 8.x-9.x.\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs32 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 After Installation:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf2 You are now ready to relaunch your applications and use your new fonts. *Remember to back up the originals on a separate disk after installation!\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

