\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Installing OpenType fonts in Windows 95/98/ME/NT4
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs32 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Overview:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural
\cf2 To use OpenType fonts on older versions of Windows, you will need Adobe Type Manager (ATM) 4.1 or later installed on your system. You can download the free version here: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.adobe.com/products/atmlight/main.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 http://www.adobe.com/products/atmlight/main.html}}.\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b \cf0 1.
\f1\b0  \'ca \cf2 Click Start>Programs>Adobe>Adobe Type Manager.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b \cf2 2.
\f1\b0  \'ca In the ATM window, click the "Fonts" tab.\
\

\f0\b 3.
\f1\b0  \'ca Navigate to the folder containing the new fonts and select them (use the CTRL key for multiples). Click "OK" and close the Fonts Control Panel.\
\

\f0\b 4.
\f1\b0  \'ca Click "Add" to install the font(s), then exit ATM.\
\

\f0\b 5.
\f1\b0  \'ca Remember to back up your new font on a separate disk!\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

